centrist stance to the point of calling his political platform
``The New Middle.'' But German society has been slow to change,
lagging behind France in flexibility and growth, far exceeding
France in wage costs. ``Germany is still an example of socialism at
work,'' said Norbert Walter, chief economist for Deutsche Bank.
</P>
<P>
   nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
