 &HT;    Gobble it up
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Why do turkeys go gobble gobble? Because they never
learned good table manners! (Hee hee!) Learn about Thanksgiving
traditions through stories, games and pictures to color at
www.night.net/thanksgiving/fun.html-ssi. Join a turkey hunt or
exercise your vocal cords with Thanksgiving songs and music. Print
out Grandpa Tucker's Thanksgiving poems to entertain your family at
dinner. When you are all done, print out a ``Thank You''
certificate.
</P>
<P>
   COSBY CREATES NEW CARTOON
</P>
<P>
   Hey, hey, hey! It's not Fat Albert, it's Little Bill _ Bill
Cosby's latest cartoon creation. The new show ``Little Bill''
follows the adventures of a 5-year-old boy and his family. Each
half-hour episode contains two complete stories. In the first show,
Little Bill is trying to find the special ``thing'' he is good at,
and he learns how much fun his imagination can be. ``Little Bill''
premieres at 8 p.m. Sunday on Nickelodeon. Write us at
nfk(at)ajc.com with your opinion.
</P>
