r f BC-TURKEY-SITES23-COX     11-22 0322
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TURKEY-SITES23-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Turkey surfing on the Web
 &HT;    By Omar L. Gallaga
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   www.turkeyfed.org _ Let's talk turkey. In fact, let's surf for
turkeys. The National Turkey Federation knows its white meat from
its drumstick. The massive site includes consumer and food service
recipes, many ``frequently asked questions'' on turkey buying and
monthly special guest chefs who trot out their turkey best. A nice
Thanksgiving spread's-worth of information.
</P>
<P>
   www.tznet.com/lwittman/turkey.html _ Why roast that turkey when
you can deep-fry it, Cajun-style, adding even more calories to your
Thanksgiving feast? ``Jim's Cajun Deep-Fried Turkey Page'' guides
you step-by-step through the deep-frying process from the initial
dip to the final presentation.
</P>
<P>
   www.canturkey.ca/trivia.htm _ Turkey facts: ``The domestic
turkey is descended from wild turkeys originally native to Southern
Ontario, parts of the U.S. and Mexico. The turkey was tamed by the
American Indian cultures in Mexico and taken from Mexico to Europe
by Spanish conquistadors early in the 16th century.'' That's just
some of what you'll find at the Canadian Turkey Marketing Agency's
Trivia Page.
</P>
<P>
   www.benjerry.com/thanksgiving/index.html _ Ben and Jerry's
Thanksgiving page will stuff you as surely as their ice cream does.
A huge variety of Thanksgiving activities, games, screen savers,
desktop patterns, history, links and background are as filling as
Cherry Garcia.
</P>
<P>
   info.pitt.edu/(tilde)lmitten/indians.html _ And let's not forget
how this whole Thanksgiving business got started. Check out Lisa
Mitten's award-winning site, which includes links to Native
American artists, programs, cultural centers and information
resources. And then, let's give thanks to the Internet for making
it all possible.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
