   LIFESTYLE/FEATURES (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-SHOPPING (Undated) _ U.S. consumers are expected to
spend a record $9.5 billion by shopping on the Internet this
holiday season. Yet Consumer Reports concluded in a 13-page
``Holiday.shop'' special report that on-line shopping has a
downside. Sites can be vague when it comes to security and shipping
costs; inventory can be thin; navigating page after page of items
can be exhausting; and ordering procedures can be Byzantine. By
PAUL GRONDAHL.
</P>
<P>
   PILLOWS (Albany, N.Y.) _ A full day's activities requires a good
night's sleep. In addition to a good mattress, you should treat
yourself to a proper pillow. All pillows come with a comfort
lifetime (approximately five to 10 years for down or feather and
six months to two years for polyester pillows) before they lose
their fluffiness and need to be replaced. By FRANCES INGRAHAM
HEINS.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-BOOKS (Undated) _ A growing number of successful,
professional women are turning to writing in their spare time,
crafting thrillers out of their chosen careers. Patricia Cornwall,
the forensic pathologist, probably opened the door farther than
anyone else, but others are quickly following, crossing the
threshold. Here are three thrillers by women authors _ read with
flawless style by screen and stage veterans _ that demonstrate the
talent in the genre. By DOUG BLACKBURN.
</P>
