<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PILLOWS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SLEEPING COMFORT STARTS WITH A GOOD PILLOW 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By FRANCES INGRAHAM HEINS  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. _ A full day's activities requires a good night's
sleep. In addition to a good mattress, you should treat yourself to
a proper pillow.
</P>
<P>
   All pillows come with a comfort lifetime (approximately five to
10 years for down or feather and six months to two years for
polyester pillows) before they lose their fluffiness and need to be
replaced. Punching the pillow as you toss and turn can also break
it down faster.
</P>
<P>
   An old or broken pillow will no longer support your neck and
spine in a proper manner.
</P>
<P>
   Perspiration and oils from your head also can mat down your
pillows, according to Pacific Coast Feather Co. in Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   Pillows filled with down offer the ultimate in adjustability and
outlast synthetic fibers. Down and feather combinations contour to
your needs, but with a bit more resistance.
</P>
<P>
   Test your current down and feather pillow by fluffing it,
squeezing out air and folding it in half (in thirds for king size).
If it unfolds to its original shape, it's fine, according to
Pacific Coast Feather. Do the same for polyester, but place a
10-ounce weight on top, such as a medium tennis shoe. A broken
pillow will remain folded.
</P>
<P>
   A good pillow will provide just the right support no matter what
position you choose for sleep, as opposed to a pillow that you have
to fit into position to be comfortable.
</P>
<P>
   If you tend to sleep on your side, choose a firm pillow; on your
back, choose a medium firm pillow; on your stomach, choose a soft
pillow.
</P>
<P>
   To test a new pillow for adjustability, push the opposing
corners into the center of the pillow. If the pillow retains its
new shape, your pillow will adjust for your personal comfort.
</P>
<P>
   When buying a bed pillow, always look for a reputable
manufacturer, as you get what you pay for. Look for pillows with
long warranties, which mean a better value.
</P>
<P>
   Always protect your bed pillows by using both a pillow protector
and a pillow case. Fluff them regularly to retain shape and absorb
fresh air.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
