<HEADLINE>
`CHINATOWN' A CLASSIC; `AUTUMN TALE' IS TOPS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Chinatown'' (25th Anniversary Edition, DVD) _
One of the best films ever made stars Jack Nicholson who is both a
private eye confused about reality and, despite a veneer of
cynicism, a rather innocent fellow. Director Roman Polanski,
screenwriter Robert Towne, Nicholson, producer Robert Evans,
production designer Richard Sylbert, and composer Jerry Goldsmith
collaborated on this seminal film. The new edition features
interviews with Evans, Polanski, and Towne on both the VHS and DVD
editions.
</P>
<P>
   ``Autumn Tale'' _ Eric Rohmer continues to make anti-MTV movies
with confident aplomb. In an age of hyperspeed cinema, Rohmer
allows his characters and situations to take their time. This
romance is filled with the familiar Rohmer details, making it one
of the best films of the year.
</P>
<P>
   ``A Zed and Two Noughts'' _ The first time I saw Peter
Greenaway's meditation I didn't have a clue as to what was going
on. Dead beasts, naked people, delectable food, and dozens of other
striking images make this an intriguing film that needs several
viewings to get part of the point.
</P>
<P>
   ``The General's Daughter'' _ The idea that this dreadful movie
actually turned a profit is a measure of just how far John
Travolta's star has rerisen.
</P>
<P>
   ``South Park'' _ If you like the TV show, you'll love the video.
If not, head north.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Nov. 30: ``Wild Wild West'' (DVD), ``Go
Fatima!,'' ``Simon Sez'' (DVD), ``Vivid'' (DVD). Dec. 7:
``Inspector Gadget,'' ``Strangers in Good Company'' (DVD). Dec. 14:
``Buena Vista Social Club'' (DVD), ``Drop Dead Gorgeous,'' ``The
Harmonists,'' ``The Red Violin'' (DVD), ``Teaching Mrs. Tingle,''
``The Very Thought of You,'' ``A Knight in Camelot.'' Dec. 21:
``Run Lola Run'' (DVD), ``American Pie'' (DVD), ``Tampopo'' (DVD),
``Summer of Sam,'' ``Ethics for the New Millennium,'' ``A Taxing
Woman'' (DVD), ``The Funeral'' (DVD), ``K-911'' (DVD), ``Supercop
2,'' ``Witness to the Mob.'' Dec. 28: ``Dudley Do-Right,'' ``Better
Than Chocolate,'' ``Desert Blue'' (DVD). Jan. 4: ``The Thomas Crown
Affair'' (DVD), ``Sayonara.'' Jan. 11: ``The Art of Buster Keaton''
(DVD), ``The Extreme Adventures of Super Dave.'' Jan. 18: ``An
Ideal Husband,'' ``The 13th Warrior,'' ``The Wood'' (DVD). Jan. 25:
``Runaway Bride.''
</P>
