<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-11-22 17:37 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8105 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-BUFFY-ANGEL23-COX     11-22 0522
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUFFY-ANGEL23-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    November sweeps brings ``Buffy'' and ``Angel'' together again
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   It was only a matter of time before Buffy the Vampire Slayer got
back with Angel, her vampire ex-lover. Actually, it was only a
matter of timing, of waiting for November sweeps and maximum
ratings bang for the buck.
</P>
<P>
   The two parted in May, soulmates who had to face the problem
that only one of them had a soul. Angel spun off to his own series,
Buffy went off to college, and the WB got two hot shows from what
used to be one.
</P>
<P>
   Tonight's super-duper-double crossover brings Angel back to
Sunnydale, Buffy's stomping and staking grounds, and then Buffy
(Sarah Michelle Gellar) goes to Los Angeles to help Angel (David
Boreanaz), in the more satisfying of the two episodes.
</P>
<P>
   The ``Buffy'' lead-off is typically fun but not spectacular. The
gang is trying to whip up Thanksgiving dinner, only to have a new
building on campus disturb a Native American burial grounds, which
summons forth a warrior spirit bent on avenging the white man's
genocide. Needless to say, lumps in the mashed potatoes soon become
the least of everyone's worries.
</P>
<P>
   There's a stronger than usual comedy quota (getting the magic
potion mixed up with the stuffing recipe, etc.) But this is served
up regularly on ``Buffy'' _ the true fans are going to be panting
for an encounter between the heroine and her hunky, broody beloved,
and they won't get it in ``Buffy'' _ Angel just lurks in the
shadows keeping an eye on her, helping out behind the scenes.
</P>
<P>
   They'll get more than they hoped for in ``Angel,'' however,
which follows on the events of ``Buffy'' but takes them in a new
direction. Buffy finds out Angel was tailing her and goes to L.A.
to tell him she's a big girl now and doesn't need him to play Mr.
Protector. Just as they're deciding yet again that no matter how
strong their attraction, their love will always be thwarted, along
comes another in the endless supply of demons with magical powers
and changes Angel from a vampire back to a human.
</P>
<P>
   As fans know (and if you're not a fan already, these intensive
episodes are not the place to start), this removes the obstacle to
their love, and pretty soon B&AMP;A are making up for lost time in a
scene involving rumpled bedsheets and chocolate ice cream that will
have ``Buff''-sters palpitating on the Internet for days to come.
</P>
<P>
   But as ``Angel'' fans also know, if you take away his
torment-of-the-undead bit, you invalidate the whole premise for the
show, and that won't do; the natural order must be restored. And
doing that, of course, means returning Buffy and Angel to their
star-crossed state, sad as it may be.
</P>
<P>
   So in two hours, you've got dinner, demons, dessert, sex,
chuckles and romantic tragedy. What more could you want? Whatever
it is, don't count on getting it until the next sweeps period, in
February.
</P>
<P>
   ``Buffy the Vampire Slayer.''
</P>
<P>
   8 tonight on the WB
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   ``Angel.''
</P>
<P>
   9 tonight on the WB
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B+
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
