   EDs: Both stories expected to move by 5 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-MOSQUE _ NAZARETH _ Catholic and Orthodix Christian
leaders, upset over the proposed construction of a Muslim mosque in
this storied city to mark the new millennium, closed the doors of
their sanctuaries to visitors and tourists Monday in protest. The
cornerstone of the mosque is expected to be laid on Tuesday, near
the Church of the Enunciation, where Mary was supposedly visited by
the angel Gabriel. Developing. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
</P>
