in the Granada Hills area of Los Angeles, Principal Jim Gwin marked
the 36th anniversary of the president's asassination with a
reminder to his students about some things Kennedy stood for. ``He
inspired the young people of the day to public service _ Vista, the
Peace Corps, that kind of thing,'' he said. It was the message in
Kennedy's inaugural address that most impressed senior Greg
Thompson: ``Ask not what your country can do for you. Ask what you
can do for your country.'' ``Instead of waiting for your handout,
