<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-DOLPHINS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Aikman, Marino given go-aheads for Thanksgiving game
 &HT;    By Rick Cantu
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ When Miami and Dallas meet Thursday afternoon,
their future Hall of Fame quarterbacks will be calling the shots.
</P>
<P>
   Troy Aikman confirmed Monday that he is fit to play in the
critical Thanksgiving Day game at Texas Stadium. Nearly 2,000 miles
away, Dan Marino also was prepared to make a comeback.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman and Marino provide an interesting subplot in a game
filled with interesting chapters. Aikman (two concussions) has
missed two games, and Marino (pinched nerve in his neck) is
returning from a five-game absence.
</P>
<P>
   The Miami-Dallas game has been hyped as Coach Jimmy Johnson's
first game at Texas Stadium since he and team owner Jerry Jones
parted ways after the 1993 season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm happy it's a short week because I won't have to hear as
many questions about it,'' Johnson said of his homecoming.
</P>
<P>
   On Monday, all attention shifted to a pair of quarterbacks who
have been missing in action.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman said he received medical advice from several physicians
in the last three weeks and concluded he has not had an
``inordinate'' amount of concussions. Aikman knows of eight
concussions in his college and pro careers, and does not consider
his return risky.
</P>
<P>
   He participated in a light workout Monday afternoon at Valley
Ranch, marking the first time he has taken the majority of snaps
since suffering concussions in consecutive games against
Indianapolis and Minneapolis.
</P>
<P>
   During his two-game absence, Jason Garrett was 1-1 filling in
for Aikman.
</P>
<P>
   The game arguably is more vital for Dallas (5-5) than Miami
(8-2). The Cowboys are 1-5 on the road and 4-0 at home. Miami has a
4-1 record with backup Damon Huard taking the snaps the past five
games.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've missed Dan, without question,'' Johnson said. ``I'm
really happy with the way Damon has played overall. But after the
first week or two, I think it finally hit him how important he was.
He's going to be a good player for us, but he's not there yet.
</P>
<P>
   ``When Dan is in the lineup, we can do some different things.
You want a mobile quarterback, but more than anything you want a
winning quarterback.''
</P>
<P>
   Johnson said Marino's return will be a game-time decision, but
it appears certain he will start. Marino practiced Monday, a sign
he is ready to play.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys, meanwhile, continue to baffle their fans by losing
second-half leads. They have led at halftime in nine of their 10
games and, in the other game, they had a 3-3 tie with the New York
Giants.
</P>
<P>
   In their five losses, Dallas has blown leads of 7-3, 17-3, 17-0,
10-0 and 3-0.
</P>
<P>
   When Coach Chan Gailey was asked about the root of those blown
leads, he said, ``If I knew the answer to that, we'd get it
fixed.''
</P>
<P>
   Gailey nixed a theory that the Cowboys are poorly conditioned.
He cited the team's 21-point fourth-quarter comeback in the season
opener in Washington as proof that his players are physically
prepared.
</P>
<P>
   Gailey shook off criticism that the Cowboys abandoned their game
plan of using running Emmitt Smith extensively during Sunday's 13-9
loss at Arizona. Smith rushed for 127 yards, but carried the
football only twice in the pivotal third quarter.
</P>
<P>
   In that span the Cowboys passed ineffectively and lost the lead.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can never please everybody, especially when you don't
win,'' the coach said. ``I still believe in keeping an offensive
balance.''
</P>
<P>
   Gailey said injuries to safety George Teague (lacerated left
hand), cornerback Kevin Smith (strained right hamstring), receiver
Jason Tucker (sprained left big toe) and tackle Erik Williams (mild
concussion) likely will not prevent them from playing Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Rick Cantu writes for the Austin American-Statesman, Austin,
Texas. E-mail: rcantu(at)statesman.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
