<P>
   (NYT23) CASABLANCA, Morocco -- Nov. 22, 1999 --
MOROCCO-BOURSE-2, 11-22 -- The trading floor of the Casablanca
Stock Exchange, with just 30 traders working in little computer
cubicles, is quiet as a church. And it is about to get even
quieter. Early next year, the trading floor is shutting down,
exchange officials say, thrusting Casablanca's small, young, but
technologically hip stock market into the growing ranks of virtual
exchanges around the world. (Joseph Treaster/New York Times Photo)
LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) CASABLANCA, Morocco -- Nov. 22, 1999 --
MOROCCO-BOURSE-1, 11-22 -- The exterior of the Casablanca Stock
