Monday. The board is expected to clear the way for the City
University of New York to begin to exclude students from its degree
programs who cannot demonstrate that they are ready to begin
``college level work'' in both mathematics and English. (Librado
Romero/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) PRINCEVILLE, N.C. -- Nov. 22, 1999 --
NC-FLOOD-HOLDOUTS-B&AMP;W-2, 11-21 -- Residents of the town, settled by
former slaves, dig their way out of a major snowstorm last century.
After recent floods in the area, some of the worst in the state's
history, Princeville's more than 2,000 citizens, many of whom are
direct descendants from the freed slaves who founded the town, are
struggling with choices that will determine whether their historic
town can ever exist again. (Edgecombe County Memorial Library/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
