<HEADLINE>
INTERNET BANKING SERVICES TO MERGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By Jason Z. Cohen 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- Internet banking services provider Digital
Insight announced Monday it will buy rival nFront Inc. for $439
million in stock.
</P>
<P>
   The addition of Atlanta-based nFront is expected to add to
Digital Insight's earnings immediately and shorten its estimated
time to profitability by three months, said Kevin McDonnell,
Digital Insight's chief financial officer.
</P>
<P>
   ``We think it's a good deal for both of the companies,''
McDonnell said. ``It combines two very complementary companies and
gives us excellent market coverage out of the box with a very
strong product offering.''
</P>
<P>
   NFront's primary customer base is small banks, while Digital
Insight's stable of customers includes mostly credit unions,
McDonnell said. The combined company has about an even number of
banks and credit unions as customers, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Digital Insight, which went public in October at an initial
offering price of $15 per share, ended trading Monday down more
than 20 percent at $39.9375 per share.
</P>
<P>
   NFront's stock gained on the merger announcement, adding 12
percent of its value to close at $21 per share.
</P>
<P>
   McDonnell said he is not concerned about Monday's dip in Digital
Insight's stock price. The company maintains a favorable long-term
view of the stock price, he said.
</P>
<P>
   The combined entity will operate as Digital Insight and be
headquartered in Calabasas, with operations continuing in nFront's
Atlanta offices.
</P>
<P>
   John Dorman, who is chairman of the board, president and chief
executive officer of Digital Insight, will serve as the company's
CEO and chairman of the board. Tripp Rackley, nFront's chairman and
CEO, will become the new entity's president and a member of the
board of directors.
</P>
<P>
   The board of directors will consist of five Digital Insight
directors and two nFront directors. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
