<HEADLINE>
IS WELLPOINT POISED FOR RUSH MERGER?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By Chris Sieroty 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- On the day that WellPoint Health Networks Inc.
announced it had enrolled its 5 millionth member in California, the
company declined to comment on a report that it is about to buy the
largest health maintenance organization in the Chicago area.
</P>
<P>
   Thousand Oaks-based WellPoint, the nation's fifth-largest HMO,
also said it now has 120,000 members in Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Crain's Chicago Business reported Monday that WellPoint is
expected to purchase Chicago's largest health maintenance
organization, Rush Prudential Health Plans.
</P>
<P>
   The deal, valued at between $225 million and $290 million, could
be announced as early as this week, Crain's said. The merger would
add Rush Prudential's 380,000 members to WellPoint's nearly 7.2
million medical and approximately 30.6 million specialty members.
</P>
<P>
   ``Wellpoint has no comment on the report,'' said company
spokesman Larry Bryant. Officials at Rush Prudential could not be
reached for comment on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Paine Webber analyst William S. McKeever said the purchase of
Rush Prudential would be in line with WellPoint's strategy to
expand its business into other areas of the country. McKeever has
rated WellPoint Health a ``buy.''
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, WellPoint on Monday announced two key enrollment
milestones. The company's California subsidiary, Blue Cross of
California, now has 5 million members enrolled in its health care
plans.
</P>
<P>
   And in Texas, Unicare Life and Health Insurance Co., the
national operating subsidiary of WellPoint Health, announced that
its enrollment in individual health plans reached the
120,000-member mark. Bryant said in four years, Unicare has become
the largest insurer of individual polices in Texas.
</P>
<P>
   ``This growth shows people really appreciate and value the
choice our plans offer to our members across the country,'' Bryant
said. WellPoint's enrollment has climbed by an average of 900,000
members annually since 1993.
</P>
<P>
   WellPoint stock closed at $63.375, down $1.1875, Monday on the
New York Stock Exchange. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
